## Additional Task Requirements
The task should be performed using a machine learning algorithm that is capable of handling categorical inputs and outputs. The algorithm should be trained on the Iris dataset and should be able to predict the species of a given iris based on its petal and sepal dimensions.

## Previous Task Results
The task should evaluate the previous task results and provide feedback on their accuracy. The feedback should be based on the task score and should indicate whether the previous task was accurate or not.

## Future Task Updates
The task should be updated to include any new features or constraints that may be added to the task. The updates should be provided in the task output and should be used to improve the accuracy of the task.

## Task Maintenance
The task should be maintained by the assistant to ensure that it continues to be accurate and up-to-date. The task should be reviewed regularly to ensure that it continues to meet the requirements of the task and that it is still relevant.

## Task Evaluation Metrics
The task should use the following evaluation metrics to evaluate its accuracy:
- Accuracy: The proportion of correct predictions out of the total number of predictions.
- Precision: The proportion of correct predictions out of the total number of positive predictions.
- Recall: The proportion of correct predictions out of the total number of actual positive instances.
- F1 Score: The harmonic mean of precision and recall.

## Task Uncertainty Handling
The task should be able to handle uncertainty in its predictions. The task should provide feedback on the uncertainty of its predictions and should be able to explain its reasoning behind its predictions.
